==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|sy}}

===Etymology===
From the same Finno-Ugric root *''sikse'' as Hungarian [[ősz]]. Cognates include Estonian [[sügis]] and North Sámi [[čakča]].

===Noun===
'''syksy'''

# [[autumn]], [[fall]].

